{meta: title Rock My Cradle Once Again}
{meta: artist Hank Williams Sr.}
{meta: composer John Bond and Billy Folger}

{start_of_verse: Verse 1}
[C]Far away from friends and loved ones
[G7]Mid the storm a soldier [C]lay
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 2}
Gathered round him all his buddies
[G7]Raised his head we heard him [C]say
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 3}
[F]There's a lamp light in the [C]window
[F]Where an angel from [C]above
[F]Gently rocked my baby [C]cradle
[G7]With such tender care and [C]love
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 4}
[F]Mother dearest darling [C]mother
[F]It would ease this awful [C]pain
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 5}
If she'd sing until I'm sleeping
[G7]Rock my cradle once [C]again
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 6}
Neath the palms tonight he's sleeping
[G7]On an island far [C]away
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 7}
Though the years pass on in sorrow
[G7]I still recall his words [C]today
{end_of_verse}

